What you need to know:

The 42-year-old former England midfielder's future at Stamford Bridge has become a hot topic, with Chelsea having lost five of their last eight league matchesLampard's emerging side are at home to Luton in the fourth round of the FA Cup on Sunday and a further slip-up against the Hatters will only add to the pressure on the Chelsea managerLampard said that turning Chelsea's form around was down to attitude as much as tactics